@startuml workflow
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

start

:Receive CLI arguments;
:Resolve input directory;
:Validate input directory exists
and is a directory;

:Resolve configuration;
note right
Defaults are overridden by
the configuration file, then
environment variables, then
command-line options.
end note

:Recursively scan project directory
for Java files;

:Read Java file contents;

:Collect available jOOQ Keys files;

:Apply jOOQ-specific inclusion and
exclusion heuristics;

:Create analysis candidates;
note right
For each retained file:
- store absolute and relative paths
- store file contents
- classify as ddl or dml-dql
- attach closest available Keys context
end note

:Resolve model provider and API key;

fork
  repeat
    :Select next candidate;
    :Build bounded model request;
    note right
    Source code is line-numbered.
    If the request is too large,
    source and Keys context are truncated.
    end note

    :Submit structured request to LLM;

    if (Request succeeds and
    response validates?) then (yes)
      :Store per-file analysis result;
    else (no)
      :Retry until configured retries
      are exhausted;
      if (Retry succeeds?) then (yes)
        :Store per-file analysis result;
      else (no)
        :Store per-file error result;
      endif
    endif
  repeat while (More candidates?) is (yes)
fork again
  :Other candidates processed
  concurrently up to configured limit;
end fork

:Sort per-file results;
:Aggregate run-level summary;
note right
Summary includes scanned Java files,
applicable files, analyzed files,
failed files, files with findings,
finding counts, distinct antipatterns,
and token usage when available.

In classification mode, finding counts
are classified antipatterns per file.
In localisation mode, finding counts
are localized occurrences.
end note

:Create CLI output object;

:Render selected output format;
note right
Supported formats:
text, JSON, CSV.
end note

if (Output file configured?) then (yes)
  :Create output directory if needed;
  :Write report to file;
else (no)
  :Print report to stdout;
endif

stop
@enduml